registration.body:
Registration is completed when a prospective User agrees to these Terms, applies for registration in the manner prescribed by the Service, and the Service approves the application. Registration for the Service is performed through authentication with a Google account.
The Service may decline to approve an application for registration if it determines that the applicant falls under any of the following, and is under no obligation to disclose the reasons:
(1) Where false information was provided in the application;
(2) Where the application is from a person who has previously violated these Terms;
(3) Where the Service otherwise determines the registration to be inappropriate.

suspension.body:
The Service may suspend or interrupt all or part of the Service without prior notice to Users if it determines that any of the following applies:
(1) When performing maintenance, inspection, or updates of the computer systems related to the Service;
(2) When provision of the Service becomes difficult due to force majeure such as earthquake, lightning, fire, power outage, or natural disaster;
(3) When computers or communication lines are stopped due to an accident;
(4) When the Service otherwise determines that provision of the Service is difficult.
The Service shall bear no responsibility whatsoever for any disadvantage or damage suffered by Users or third parties resulting from the suspension or interruption of the Service.

restriction.body:
The Service may, without prior notice, restrict all or part of a User's use of the Service or cancel their registration if the User falls under any of the following:
(1) Where the User violates any provision of these Terms;
(2) Where it is found that there are false facts in the registered information;
(3) Where there is no response to contact from the Service for a certain period;
(4) Where there has been no use of the Service for a certain period since the last use;
(5) Where the Service otherwise determines the use of the Service to be inappropriate.
The Service shall bear no responsibility for any damage caused to Users by actions taken by the Service under this Article.

disclosure.body:
When requested by an individual to disclose personal information, the Service will disclose it to the individual without delay. However, if disclosure would fall under any of the following, the Service may decide not to disclose all or part of it, and will notify the individual to that effect without delay:
(1) Where there is a risk of harming the life, body, property, or other rights or interests of the individual or a third party;
(2) Where there is a risk of significantly impeding the proper conduct of the Service's business;
(3) Where it would otherwise violate laws and regulations.
